      <span class="Documentation-sinceVersionVersion">go1.18</span>
    
  </span>
</h4>

    
    <div class="Documentation-declaration">
      <pre>func (c *F) Logf(format <a href="/builtin#string">string</a>, args ...<a href="/builtin#any">any</a>)</pre>
    </div>
  <p>Logf formats its arguments according to the format, analogous to <a href="/fmt#Printf">fmt.Printf</a>, and
records the text in the error log. A final newline is added if not provided. For
tests, the text will be printed only if the test fails or the -test.v flag is
set. For benchmarks, the text is always printed to avoid having performance
depend on the value of the -test.v flag.
It is an error to call Logf after a test or benchmark returns.
</p>

  

